---
title: Honey Thyme Pork Tenderloin with Roasted Sweet Potatoes & Brussels Sprouts
description: A honey glaze may sound like something that goes with dessert, but mild-tasting pork loves a sweet sauce too, especially one that has a few savory elements in it for contrast. In this recipe, you’ll be folding an extra-large drizzle of honey into a rich, savory pan sauce, then spooning it onto pork tenderloin (and the roasted sweet potatoes and Brussels sprouts served alongside, if you like).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/60ae4e31c3111e245f25bed5-8152140d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-thyme-pork-tenderloin-60ae4e31c3111e245f25bed5-93e34dc2.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-thyme-pork-tenderloin-60ae4e31c3111e245f25bed5
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
